edu.ucdavis.cstars.client.layers

Class KMLLayer

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.gwt.core.client.JavaScriptObject
      • edu.ucdavis.cstars.client.layers.Layer
        • edu.ucdavis.cstars.client.layers.KMLLayer

  • public class KMLLayer
extends Layer
    The KMLLayer class is used to create a layer based on a KML file (.kml,.kmz). KML is an XML-based file format used to represent geographic features. Features from the KML file are accessible via the api so you can query features and use them as input to geometry or geoprocessing services.
    Author:
    Justin Merz

      • getLayers

        public final com.google.gwt.core.client.JsArray<Layer> getLayers()
        Get an array of map layers that were created to draw placemarks, ground and screen overlays. The returned array can have instances of the following layer types: FeatureLayer or MapImageLayer. This method can be used to override the renderer for feature layers.
        Returns:
        JsArray

      • addRefreshHandler

        public final void addRefreshHandler(RefreshHandler handler)
        Set the refresh event handler.
        Parameters:
        handler - - Fired after the layer is refreshed. If the layer represents a network link it is automatically refreshed based on the network link parameters defined in the linkInfo property. Layers can be explicitly refreshed by calling the refresh method.
